    "## Creating Interaction Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Interaction features combine two variables mathematically to capture\n",
    "relationships that individual features miss. Created on training set\n",
    "only — not applied to Experiment 1 baseline OLS.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is an interaction feature?\n",
    "A single feature tells the model one thing. An interaction feature\n",
    "tells the model how two things work **together**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example from this dataset:\n",
    "- clicks alone tell us how many people engaged\n",
    "- conversions alone tell us how many people acted\n",
    "- clicks × conversions tells us which campaigns were\n",
    "  both popular AND effective simultaneously\n",
    "\n",
    "### Three interactions created\n",
    "1. **clicks × conversions** — campaigns popular AND effective\n",
    "2. **conversions / ad_spend** — spend efficiency (conversions per dollar)\n",
    "3. **impressions × CTR** — effective reach (reach × engagement rate)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why not used in Experiment 1\n",
    "Baseline OLS must run with the original features first to establish\n",
    "a reference R². Adding interactions before the baseline muddies\n",
    "interpretation — we cannot know if improvements come from the\n",
    "model or the new features.\n",
    "\n",
    "### When will they be used\n",
    "Experiment 2 — if correlation analysis shows interaction features\n",
    "outperform their original components, they will replace or\n",
    "supplement them in the refined model."
   ]
  },
